    "page": "230",
    "excerpt": "Russell Speeder's Car Wash & Shell Station | 1429 East Putnam Avenue, Old Greenwich, CT 06870 | $20,000,000 | $2,688,000 | $4,000,000 | Est. 0.85 | Old Greenwich conveyor tunnel car wash and Shell station acquisition record. The scanned memo cites 5,600 members, $40 monthly memberships, and EBITDA over $4.0M.",
    "full_text": "EXECUTIVE SUMMARY \nAn investor group consisting of The Morgan Group and Russell Speeder's Car Wash (collectively known as the \"Sponsor\" or \n\"Borrower\") is seeking first mortgage financing in the amount of $13,000,000 ($650 PSF / 65% LTC) to finance the acquisition of a \nconveyorized-tunnel car wash and Shell gasoline station located at 1429 East Putnam Avenue, Old Greenwich, CT 06870 (\"The \nProperty\"). With a purchase price of $20,000,000 ($1,000 PSF), the Property spans roughly 20,000 SF and is fully-outfitted with \ncomplete car wash systems, equipment, car wash tunnels, equipment rooms, enhanced computer systems, and self-serve \nvacuums. The asset boasts multiple revenue streams due to its attached oil change and emissions testing center, convenience \nstore, and Shell gasoline station. As of August 2021, the Property has 5,600 members each paying $40 per month for the use of its \nconveyorized-car wash. Generating an additional $2,688,000 per year, the asset will conclude 2021 with an EBITDA of over \n$4,000,000. Given Its prime location and addition of the Russell Speeder's brand, the Property is poised to grow Its already-high \ncustomer volumes and further increase its subscription-base. Russell Speeder's subscription-based business model has resulted in \nunparalleled customer retention and loyalty, with an overwhelming majority of customers renewing this unique 'Netflix-type' \nsubscription service on a monthly basis. More specifically, subscription wash revenue accounts for approximately 85% of total wash \nrevenue across their entire portfolio. A direct result of the firm's exceptional management team and operation practices, coupled \nwith the brand's top-of-the-line customer service and quality care, the Sponsor has successfully grown cash flows throughout its \nportfolio in a significant manner since 2016. In 2019, Russell Speeder's ranked #19 on Car Wash.com's 'Top 50 U.S. Conveyor Chain' \nlist, an annual account of the leading operators of conveyor/tunnel carwashes nationwide. The Property is located in proximity to \nseveral major arteries and thoroughfares within the greater Fairfield County, resulting in high visibility, vehicle traffic counts, and \npositive sales volumes. The loan proceeds will be used to acquire the property and cover associated closing costs. \nThe Sponsorship group boasts decades of industry experience and proven track records: The Morgan Group, led by principals \nStuart Morgan (over thirty-eight (38) years of industry experience), Scott Morgan, and Ryan Morgan, is a real estate Investment \nand management company that owns and manages residential apartment buildings throughout the Greater New York City Area \nand retail properties in various markets throughout the country; Russell Speeder's Car Wash is a nationally recognized expert in the \ndevelopment, management, and operation of automotive businesses. Active in the industry for more than thirty-two (32) years, \nMichael Shullman currently owns and operates twenty-three (23) facilities in six (6) states and has been involved over forty-six (46) \nprojects throughout his career under a variety of brands including Mobil, Phillips 66, Shell, Valvoline, and Russell Speeders. \nSOURCES & USES Amount %Total P.SF1\nSources \nFirst Mortgage: \nBorrower Equity: \n$13,000,000 \n$7,330,000 \n63.9% \n36.1% \n$650 \n$367 \nTotal Sources $20,330,000 100.0% $1,017 \nUses \nPurchase Price: \nClosing Costs (2.50902: \n$20,000,000 \n$330,000 \n98.4% \n1.6% \n$1,000 \n$17 \nTotal Uses $20,330,000 100.0% $1,017 \n(11 Based on 20,000 SF. \n(21 Casing Costs are based off of 2.596 of First Mortgage Financing. \n8 \nBLACKBEAR ASSET MANAGEMEN1 THE MORGAN GROUP \nRussell Speeder's",
